<section id="privacy" class="band">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="head">
      <p>Privacy</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <h2>Everything lives on your phone.</h2>
      <div class="text">
        <p>There's no account and no sign-up. Every medication, every schedule, every dose you log stays on your phone.</p>
        <p>The one exception: when you scan a label, that photo travels over an encrypted connection just long enough to be read. Once it's turned into your digital label, the photo is discarded and our server keeps nothing.</p>
        <p class="strong">That's the whole story. No analytics, no trackers, no data to sell, because we don't have any to begin with.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .band {
    background: var(--slate);
    color: var(--paper);
    margin-top: 52px;
    padding-block: 40px 48px;
  }

  .head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--slate-line);
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 26px;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.4fr;
    gap: 40px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3.4vw, 34px);
    max-width: 15ch;
    color: var(--terracotta);
  }

  .text p {
    color: var(--slate-text);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  .text p.strong {
    color: var(--paper);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 18px;
    }

    h2 {
      max-width: none;
    }
  }
</style>
